review_blob: Just came back from Mount Rushmore with a case.  16 oz aluminum bottle..really good brown ale.  Dark with a thick tan head, light body but consistant with style.  Malty but balanced by the hops with a slight lingering bitterness.  Reminded me of a porter light.  It worked for me.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Love this stuff.  Nothing beats it floating on Bass or Harp Lager.  Love the smooth texture and slight bitterness.  If I had to only have one beer to drink this would be it.
Bold beer.  At first it is overwhelming until you get used to it.  Malty aroma and ballanced finsih.
